@/*
  Generates code to scan the inverse of the given assertion.

  Since an assertion is (by definition) merely returns a boolean
  asserting one thing or another (without advancing the read pointer
  or other side effects), we can just call the assertion function
  and return its inverse.

 */@

@parameter: const productions &prds @
@parameter: const std::string &assertion @

{
    return !custom_scanner_@assertion@(*reader);
}
